Patch 05 — skip the "Configured to not listen anywhere" exit on mobile builds.

Dazzle runs Valkey in-process. Every directCommand / directPipeline /
primitive call routes through dazzle_direct_init's fake client
(CLIENT_ID_CACHED_RESPONSE, set up in InitServerLast), which does not
need a socket, TCP port, or unix socket to operate. With `--port 0`
and no `--unixsocket`, upstream Valkey aborts in initListeners()
before the fake-client bring-up runs, even though nothing in the
embedded path depends on `listen_fds > 0`.

This patch turns the bail-out into a warning-only path when compiled
for VALKEY_IOS or __ANDROID__. Mainline builds (the default) keep the
existing guard so the server still refuses to boot silently when
mis-configured on a standalone host.

diff --git a/src/server.c b/src/server.c
--- a/src/server.c
+++ b/src/server.c
@@ -3131,10 +3131,19 @@ void initListeners(void) {
         listen_fds += listener->count;
     }

     if (listen_fds == 0) {
+#if defined(VALKEY_IOS) || defined(__ANDROID__)
+        /* dazzle: the in-process fake-client path
+         * (see core/transport/dazzle_transport.c — CLIENT_ID_CACHED_RESPONSE)
+         * serves every directCommand / directPipeline call, so a zero
+         * listener count is the intentional "in-process only" mode.
+         * Log for diagnostics and keep going instead of exiting. */
+        serverLog(LL_NOTICE, "Dazzle in-process mode: no listener configured, using JNI pipe only.");
+#else
         serverLog(LL_WARNING, "Configured to not listen anywhere, exiting.");
         exit(1);
+#endif
     }
 }

 /* Some steps in server initialization need to be done last (after modules
  * are loaded).
